    • Method Detail

      • unparseableExpression

        void unparseableExpression(Exception parseException,
                         String exprName)
        Called if an expression could not be parsed.

        If the parse error occurred while parsing a named subexpression, the name of the subexpression will also be passed as the exprName parameter. Otherwise (that is, if the main expression could not be parsed), exprName will be null.

        Parameters:
        parseException - the exception that was thrown while trying to parse
        exprName - the name of the named subexpression, or null if the parse error occurred while parsing the main expression.

      • undefinedIdentifier

        void undefinedIdentifier(String id,
                       String exprName)
        Called if an undefined identifier was referenced.
        Parameters:
        id - the undefined identifier that was referenced
        exprName - the name of the named subexpression, or null if the parse error occurred while parsing the main expression.

      • undefinedSubExpression

        void undefinedSubExpression(String subExprName,
                          String exprName)
        Called if an undefined subexpression was referenced.
        Parameters:
        subExprName - the name of the undefined subexpression that was referenced
        exprName - the name of the named subexpression, or null if the parse error occurred while parsing the main expression.
